#compdef bita
# =============================================================================
# bita — Erik Olsson's "Differential file synchronization over
#         HTTP" — a Rust-based content-defined chunking +
#         deduplication tool similar to rsync-over-HTTP but
#         designed for IoT firmware updates + container image
#         distribution + large-file CDN delivery.  Distinct
#         features:
#           - CONTENT-DEFINED CHUNKING via rolling hash (BuzHash
#             or RollSum), automatically detecting chunk
#             boundaries based on content rather than fixed-
#             size offsets
#           - HTTP RANGE REQUEST cloning — bita downloads ONLY
#             the chunks that differ from a local "seed" file,
#             using HTTP byte ranges to fetch the deltas
#           - SEED MATCHING — supply local files (or stdin) as
#             potential delta sources; bita identifies matching
#             chunks via per-chunk hash lookup
#           - IN-PLACE OUTPUT — `--seed-output` flag lets bita
#             use the OUTPUT FILE itself as a seed, updating
#             it incrementally
#           - HEADER + OUTPUT CHECKSUM VERIFICATION — bita
#             verifies archive header integrity and final
#             output integrity
#         Used for IoT/embedded firmware updates (atomic
#         partition swapping with delta downloads), container
#         image distribution (skopeo + bita layer caching),
#         and CDN edge cache fill optimization.  bitar (the
#         library) is the reusable core; bita is the CLI tool.
#
# Author:  Erik Olsson (oll3 on GitHub) — Swedish embedded
#          systems engineer; launched bita in 2019 as the
#          firmware-update tool he wanted for industrial IoT
#          devices.  Continues active maintenance with periodic
#          format-version updates.
# Source:  https://github.com/oll3/bita
#          https://github.com/oll3/bita/blob/master/src/main.rs
#          https://github.com/oll3/bita/blob/master/src/cli.rs
# CLI:     src/cli.rs — uses `clap::{Arg, Command, ArgAction,
#          value_parser}` builder API (already documented in
#          taxonomy).  Headline observability library: `fern`
#          for chained-dispatch structured logging throughout
#          the chunker + HTTP fetcher + archive verifier.
# Library: fern (daboross/fern)
#          ("Simple, efficient logging for Rust" — David Ross
#           (daboross) — released 2014 as a CHAINABLE DISPATCH
#           logger for the Rust `log` crate facade.  fern's
#           central abstraction is the `Dispatch` value —
#           a configurable log handler that can chain to other
#           dispatchers, child outputs, custom formatters,
#           level filters, or per-target overrides:
#             - format(closure) — set log entry format
#             - level(LevelFilter) — set base level
#             - level_for(target, level) — per-target level
#             - chain(impl io::Write) — append to writer
#             - chain(Dispatch) — chain to child dispatcher
#             - apply() — install as global logger
#           Multiple dispatchers can route the same record to
#           different destinations with different formats/
#           filters — analogous to slog's drain chain but
#           lighter-weight + tied to the `log` facade.)
# License: MIT (bita); MIT OR Apache-2.0 (fern)
# Status:  bita — 289+ stars on oll3/bita, periodic maintenance
#          with format-version updates; fern — 1300+ stars on
#          daboross/fern (top-300 Rust GitHub project), 40M+
#          all-time crates.io downloads, foundational logger
#          for many production Rust services from the 2015-2020
#          pre-tracing era — used by Helix editor +
#          vaultwarden + Spotifyd + UAD + many embedded-Rust
#          + iced-GUI tools.
#
