#
# Subcommands:
#   compress    Compress a file or stream into a bita archive
#   clone       Clone a remote (or local) archive — unpacks
#                while cloning
#   diff        Show the differential between two files
#   info        Show archive info (metadata, chunks, etc)
#
# Five-axis distinctness from every other documented Rust logger:
#
#   1. CHAINABLE Dispatch BUILDER — Every other documented Rust
#      logger uses different composition models (env_logger
#      builder, slog drains, tracing Subscribers).  fern uses
#      a chainable Dispatch builder.
#
#   2. PARENT/CHILD Dispatch HIERARCHY — Every other documented
#      Rust logger has flat or layered composition.  fern
#      supports arbitrary parent/child Dispatch trees.
#
#   3. PROGRAMMATIC PER-TARGET LEVEL OVERRIDES — Every other
#      documented Rust logger uses env-var-driven or single
#      filter functions.  fern exposes `.level_for(target,
#      level)` as a primary builder method for per-target
#      programmatic levels.
#
#   4. RAW-RECORD CLOSURE FORMAT API — Every other documented
#      Rust logger has limited format hooks.  fern's `.format()`
#      takes a closure with full access to file/line/target/
#      level/module-path via the Record value.
#
#   5. COMPANION fern::colors LEVEL-COLOR HELPER — Every other
#      documented Rust logger requires manual ANSI escape
#      handling.  fern ships fern::colors::ColoredLevelConfig
#      for integrated level coloring.
#
